headline: How The Narrative Around Ford Motor (F) Is Shifting With The 2026 EV Reset
summary: What Is Actually Changing in Ford’s Price Target Story Ford’s updated narrative keeps the core fair value anchor steady at US$13.76 per share, while making only very small tweaks to the assumptions that feed into that valuation. The discount rate is trimmed slightly and the long term revenue outlook moves from about a 1.11% decline to about a 1.10% decline, reflecting research that sees Ford’s 2026 setup and EV reset as a touch more predictable but still not free of execution risk. headline: Ford’s EV Reset Puts Hybrids Geely Talks And Valuation In Focus
summary: Ford Motor (NYSE:F) is pivoting away from fully electric vehicles and has recorded a $19.5b write down on EV related assets. The company is shifting emphasis toward hybrids and extended range EVs in response to changing demand and policy signals. Ford is in talks with Geely to potentially share factory space in Europe and work together on technology development. For investors watching NYSE:F, this marks a meaningful reset in how Ford is approaching electrification and where it is putting...
